          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Chicken thighs"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "1704cd59-47ce-4543-8576-bd22d628f355",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Seasonings"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "bde3c679-52ab-4067-a361-91d79f8a8d63",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Jarred Artichoke Hearts + liquid"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "8c9fd285-859f-44c9-844f-ed81904fb249",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Julienne Cut Sun-Dried Tomatoes"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "5f4fdf6d-36a9-40a0-9f53-40b023371298",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Garlic"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "bb3c0584-33a8-46f0-938f-f8cdb8e590a7",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO MAKE THIS CROCK POT CHICKEN THIGHS RECIPE:"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "85d46a20-ec33-4aaa-b965-9b4527691f07",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Start by spraying a 6-quart crock pot/slow cooker with cooking spray."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "6f3458b6-f2f8-49bc-9968-c73402c4a9dd",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Next, season chicken thighs with salt, pepper, and dried oregano. Transfer chicken thighs to the slow cooker in one layer."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "cf2d67d8-806c-44bf-88ca-bd3819673fce",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Then, layer the artichoke hearts over the chicken and sprinkle with garlic. Take a 1/3-cup of the liquid from the jar with the artichoke hearts and pour it over the top."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "74fa8a10-f5f2-47c1-9d55-16c4c98d36cc",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Next, cover; cook on HIGH for 4 to 4-1/2 hours, or on LOW for about 6 hours."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "4bfa17a1-a5f9-4c11-b2ae-4b2cbc35b69f",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add in the sun-dried tomatoes 30 minutes before chicken is done cooking."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ddc22e08-ec42-42c6-85a1-923b818e9725",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Finally, sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "99c3132a-6eb4-40e6-8972-cc100aef452a",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "70e45944-a5c1-4fe6-967b-1b6dd9d3ea8d",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I USE CHICKEN BREASTS INSTEAD?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "b508471c-14d9-4188-b573-c53741cb423c",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Yes, you can absolutely use chicken breasts, but keep in mind that chicken breasts will need less time cooking, so start checking around 5-hour mark if cooking on LOW, and around the 3-hour mark if cooking on HIGH."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "868f6be3-221a-4b51-b0a6-f7b8ceb62aac",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I USE BONE-IN CHICKEN THIGHS?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f7b0bde0-abe3-4b99-a535-7e9a8476941f",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Yes, using bone-in chicken thighs is fine. They might take a bit longer to cook; about 20 minutes longer in the crock pot."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "70519c9b-bac4-4adf-91a6-a57e5c364310",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "CAN I DOUBLE THE RECIPE?"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "1c65c0bf-3303-4f8f-96aa-3be945fc0c8b",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "I have always read not to use too many pieces of meat in a slow cooker. I think up to 6 is a good number, maybe even 8, depending on their size, but anything more than that might get a bit crowded. You want them all in one layer, slightly overlapping so to make room for the rest of the ingredients."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ec4a52d8-b27c-4ffb-a5c2-8c8b120cad65",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO STORE CROCK POT CHICKEN THIGHS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "12c49826-f42f-4282-98bc-b6dca78cce8b",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Your crock pot chicken thighs should be cooled and refrigerated 2 hours after cooking."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "de8a4f12-4ea4-4005-bea0-16085a9c49e7",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Keep them stored in your fridge in an airtight container for 3 to 4 days."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "57d7ebc9-7554-46f8-826e-710019e64fde",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "You can also freeze them. Let the chicken thighs cool completely; transfer to a freezer bag and place in the freezer. Keep frozen for up to 3 months."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "f81ec1e4-f9c8-4847-bd20-5a39b0b87984",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "HOW TO REHEAT CHICKEN THIGHS"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "d7cf9d75-a2c5-4270-aca4-4287a3a7a823",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place chicken thighs on a baking sheet and reheat in a 350\u02daF oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "26c7fc9f-6b9b-45a1-9cc5-974a35b86adb",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "TIPS FOR USING YOUR CROCKPOT"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "69460464-5913-4f36-b6b7-9351e346f0a9",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Use the right size crock pot."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "2391628c-2021-4077-a114-2b2f661d83d0",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Coating the inside of the crock pot with a non-stick spray can prevent the need for scrubbing later."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ce7c0a68-c79a-48a5-b9a5-faf192e408ba",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "For most crock pots, the high setting is about 280\u02daF, and the low setting is around 170\u02daF."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "2bbe9611-9741-4420-951a-c44101a553bc",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Cooking on HIGH for one hour is about equal to cooking on the low setting for two hours."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "e29c91a2-c25d-4615-a666-44fe122aa9a0",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add fresh herbs at the end to keep flavors bright and fresh."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "67e30f32-e81d-47b3-a0b2-754b8269a266",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place hard vegetables, like potatoes, carrots, and other root vegetables at the bottom of the slow cooker where they will have more moisture and cook thoroughly."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "b5fab83c-0d0a-4107-a293-e00e1a40a3ec",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Use cheaper cuts of meat. Inexpensive cuts of meat are often high in fat or connective tissue, both of which break down during long hour cooking methods."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "7ec04a11-2017-4a5e-bcd7-5ffd455f6066",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add dairy at the end. Milk, cream, and other dairy products can break down and coagulate if overheated. Stir the dairy products into crock pot in the last 15-30 minutes, so it has just enough time to heat through."
        }
      ],
      "instruction": "See original recipe for details."
    }
  ]
}